.TH "cma_ib_acquire_dev" 9 "cma_ib_acquire_dev" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cma_ib_acquire_dev \- Acquire cma device, port and SGID attribute
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cma_ib_acquire_dev
.BI "(struct rdma_id_private *id_priv "  ","
.BI "const struct rdma_id_private *listen_id_priv "  ","
.BI "struct cma_req_info *req "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "id_priv" 12
cm id to bind to cma device
.IP "listen_id_priv" 12
listener cm id to match against
.IP "req" 12
Pointer to req structure containaining incoming
request information
\fBcma_ib_acquire_dev\fP acquires cma device, port and SGID attribute when
rdma device matches for listen_id and incoming request. It also verifies
that a GID table entry is present for the source address.
Returns 0 on success, or returns error code otherwise.
